Sentencas: Based on the conventional interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta, a novel ceramic interconnect for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells was developed.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9

Sentencas: In the air, the electrical conductivities of La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta + 5%Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 at 600, 700 and 800 degrees C were 96.7, 146.3 and 687.8 S cm(-1), respectively, which increased significantly as compared with La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta under the same conditions.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9

Sentencas: Similarly, in pure hydrogen, La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta + 3%Ce0.8SM0.2O1.9 possessed the maximal electrical conductivities which were 4.2, 5.3 and 7.1 S cm(-1), respectively at 600, 700 and 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9

Sentencas: The crystal structures Of La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta, La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta + 5%Ce0.8SM0.2O1.9 and La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta + 10%Ce-0.8 Sm0.2O1.9 were single phase with hexagonal symmetry, cubic phase plus some doped ceria impurity and orthorhombic phase plus some doped ceria impurity, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9

Sentencas: The difference between the crystal structures may account for the difference between the electrical conductivities.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities and sinterability, of La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta were increased by introducing Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9, whereas the other properties were not influenced.
Titulo: Preparation and electrical behavior study of the ceramic interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ with CeO2-based electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9
